  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-6 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Twelve factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels; one factor (Equivalency of input parameters) is marked not-applicable with thorough rationale explaining why the factor does not apply to this single-device, single-fluid benchmark study. Decision: Accepted. Provenance chain is complete back to foundational FDA benchmark experimental data.",
